1. Study Design & Demographics
Study Classification: Vaccine Toxicology
Primary Focus: immunogenicity and local tolerance
Key Endpoints (prioritized):
  • Immunogenicity (antibody response)
  • Injection site reactions (macro/microscopic)
  • Systemic toxicity (body weight, clinical signs)
  • Clinical pathology (hematology, chemistry)
  • Organ weights and histopathology
Study Type: REPEAT DOSE TOXICITY
Species/Strain: RABBIT NEW ZEALAND
Age: 12-14 WEEKS
Total Animals: 40 (20M / 20F)
Route: INTRAMUSCULAR
Dosing Duration: P30D
Recovery: P3W
Period: 2017-09-26 → 2018-03-29

Control 0 vp/dose Recovery [Control]: 10 animals (5M/5F)

  • Study Design: This was a repeat dose toxicity study (Vaccine Toxicology) in RABBIT NEW ZEALAND (40 animals) via intramuscular administration. Primary focus: immunogenicity and local tolerance.
  • Mortality: All animals survived to scheduled sacrifice.
  • Body Weights: No significant treatment-related effects.
  • Body Temperature: Statistically significant temperature differences were observed between groups.
